snippet: An assault on a provincial police headquarters in Kirkuk by a suicide car bomber and other attackers left at least 35 people dead and dozens wounded, the police said.
abstract: Assault on a provincial police headquarters in northern Iraqi city of Kirkuk by a suicide car bomber and other attackers leaves at least 35 people dead and dozens wounded.

byline.contributor: An employee of The New York Times contributed reporting from Kirkuk, Iraq.

lead_paragraph: An assault on a provincial police headquarters in Kirkuk by a suicide car bomber and other attackers left at least 35 people dead and dozens wounded, the police said.

headline.main: Dozens Die in Attack on Police in Iraqi City
headline.print_headline: Dozens Die In Attack On Police In Iraqi City
